  "distance": "305.066 km (189.559 miles)",
  "event_preview": "Shanghai International Circuit measures 5.451 km (3.387 mi) and features 16 turns in Jiading, Shanghai, China. The circuit hosts the 2025 Chinese Grand Prix as Round 2 of the season - the first Sprint weekend of the year. Designed by Hermann Tilke and opened in 2004, the layout is instantly recognisable by its signature Turns 1-2, a tightening 270-degree right-hander that demands constant micro-adjustments from the drivers, and one of the longest straights on the calendar - a 1.2 km blast between Turns 13 and 14 that serves as the primary overtaking zone. The circuit returned to the calendar only in 2024 after a four-year COVID-enforced absence, and will also host the opening Sprint of the 2025 season. The official race lap record has stood since the very first edition of the event - 1:32.238, set by Michael Schumacher for Ferrari in 2004 - while the all-time qualifying record belongs to Sebastian Vettel, who clocked a 1:31.095 for Red Bull in Q3 during the 2018 weekend.",
  "tyre_compounds": "Tyre supplier Pirelli brought the C2, C3, and C4 tyre compounds.",
